4. Matters not to be dealt with in a meeting through video conferencing or other audio visual means.-(1) The
following matters shall not be dealt with in any meeting held through video conferencing or other audio visual
means.-
(i) the approval of the annual financial statements;
(ii) the approval of the Board’s report;
(iii) the approval of the prospectus;
(iv) the Audit Committee Meetings for consideration of accounts; and
(v) the approval of the matter relating to amalgamation, merger, demerger, acquisition and takeover.
